## Design decisions (none new in Phase 0)

All design decisions were confirmed in the
prior grilling session and the Phase 5a check
above. No new decisions. One design note that
emerged during implementation:

- **`KnowledgeErrorV1` field access**: The 3
  common fields (`topic`, `record_id`,
  `reason`) are accessed via
  `pub fn topic() -> Option<&str>`,
  `pub fn record_id() -> Option<Uuid>`,
  `pub fn reason() -> &str` accessors on the
  enum. Rust's struct-variant enum fields are
  not directly accessible by name (you must
  pattern-match the variant), so the
  accessors provide "direct access" semantics
  for workflows and the audit dashboard.
  This is a Rust-language design choice, not
  a deviation from the PRD/TRD (which said
  "the three common fields are public for
  direct access" — the accessors are the way
  to make that work in Rust).

